<paragraph blockId="245.[151,1436,1764,1944]" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis box="[196,449,1803,1827]" italics="true" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
: The absence of a postcubital fork, combined with only 2 sensilla clavata, a tongueshaped inferior volsella and the long anal point without setae characterize the male imago.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="245.[151,1436,1764,1944]" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis box="[196,316,1881,1905]" italics="true" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">Etymology</emphasis>
: From the Latin 
<emphasis box="[517,595,1882,1905]" italics="true" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">caritus</emphasis>
, lacking, devoid of, referring to the lack of numerous sensilla clavata or apical spine on the third palpomere and the lack of the postcubital fork.
</paragraph>
