<paragraph blockId="246.[151,1436,1757,1980]" lastBlockId="247.[151,1436,158,221]" lastPageId="247" lastPageNumber="248" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">
All measurements and ratios within the range of variation of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[861,1033,1796,1820]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Pseudosmittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="246" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevifurcata">
<emphasis box="[861,878,1797,1820]" italics="true" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[895,1033,1796,1820]" italics="true" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">brevifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the following exceptions and additions: Wing (
<figureCitation box="[347,457,1835,1859]" captionStart="FIGURE 92" captionStartId="246.[151,250,1658,1681]" captionTargetBox="[280,1260,213,1633]" captionTargetId="figure-149@246.[226,1360,198,1634]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 92. Pseudosmittia carita sp. n., male. A—wing; B—head; C—third palpomere; D—cibarial pump and stipes; E— virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288581/files/figure.png" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">Fig. 92 A</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity box="[550,653,1835,1859]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.9" pageId="246" pageNumber="247" unit="mm" value="0.89">0.89 mm</quantity>
. Total length/wing length 2.41. Wing length/length of profemur 2.41. AR 1.08. Clypeus apparently with 4 setae. Third palpomere (
<figureCitation box="[828,935,1874,1898]" captionStart="FIGURE 92" captionStartId="246.[151,250,1658,1681]" captionTargetBox="[280,1260,213,1633]" captionTargetId="figure-149@246.[226,1360,198,1634]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 92. Pseudosmittia carita sp. n., male. A—wing; B—head; C—third palpomere; D—cibarial pump and stipes; E— virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288581/files/figure.png" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">Fig. 92 C</figureCitation>
) with 2 sensilla clavata, fourth palpomere 75 µm long, fifth 135 µm long. Dorsocentrals 13, prealars 5. Costal extension 54 µm long, no postcubital fork, R without setae. Hind tibia 37 µm wide at apex. Tarsomere 5 of middle leg 41 µm long. Anal point (
<figureCitation box="[1245,1349,1955,1979]" captionStart="FIGURE 91" captionStartId="244.[151,250,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[332,1242,273,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-191@244.[321,1263,258,1738]" captionTargetPageId="244" captionText="FIGURE 91. Pseudosmittia albipennis (Goetghebuer). A–D. Male. A—wing; B—hypopygium, dorsal aspect; C—hypopygium, ventral aspect.; D—gonostylus. E, F. Female. female. E—wing; F—genitalia, dorsal view. G, H. Pupa. G—posterior tergites; H—posterior sternites. I–L. Larva. I—antenna; J—premandible; K—mandible; L—mentum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288577/files/figure.png" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">Fig. 91 F</figureCitation>
) 57 µm long, tapering, with concave sides, with microtrichia to apex. Laterosternite with 2 setae. Virga (
<figureCitation box="[1241,1347,158,182]" captionStart="FIGURE 92" captionStartId="246.[151,250,1658,1681]" captionTargetBox="[280,1260,213,1633]" captionTargetId="figure-149@246.[226,1360,198,1634]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 92. Pseudosmittia carita sp. n., male. A—wing; B—head; C—third palpomere; D—cibarial pump and stipes; E— virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288581/files/figure.png" pageId="247" pageNumber="248">Fig. 92 E</figureCitation>
) 18 µm long. Inner margin of gonocoxite (
<figureCitation box="[537,641,197,221]" captionStart="FIGURE 92" captionStartId="246.[151,250,1658,1681]" captionTargetBox="[280,1260,213,1633]" captionTargetId="figure-149@246.[226,1360,198,1634]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 92. Pseudosmittia carita sp. n., male. A—wing; B—head; C—third palpomere; D—cibarial pump and stipes; E— virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288581/files/figure.png" pageId="247" pageNumber="248">Fig. 92 F</figureCitation>
) with orally directed curled microtrichia. Gonostylus curved at apex.
</paragraph>
